The paper deals with the task of ranking insights extracted from multi-dimensional tables, which involves natural language processing, information retrieval, and machine learning techniques. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.DB (Databases) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a neural ranking model and a memory network model, which are both related to artificial intelligence and machine learning, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category as well. Finally, the paper also reports experimental results and evaluation metrics, which are common in the field of machine learning and data analysis, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category.
